Carolina White https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carolina_White 0 Carolina White (May 23, 1886 – October 5, 1961) was an actress and opera singer who appeared with Enrico Caruso in one of only two movies the tenor made; My Cousin. Miss White also recorded for the gramophone.
